In re Alexander. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 28,1889.) Appeal from, special term, New York county.

Argued before Van P. and Brady and JJ.

James A. Deerimg, for appellant. George L. Sterling, for respondent. Motion by Annie N. Alexander to reduce an assessment to the extent which it is alleged to exceed the limitation fixed by statute. Motion denied, and applicant appeals. Van Brunt, P. J.

For the reasons assigned in the opinion in Re Wheelock, ante, 890, .(herewith decided,) the order appealed from in this case must he affirmed, with costs. All concur.
